d a \"RECYCLE CORE ENCLAVE\" button with full functionality in the AI Operations health monitor and a dynamic sparkline in `AnalyticsPanel` that polls every 2 seconds, offering real-time updates. Micro-hover states, like button scaling and cryptographic signature highlights on invoice verifications, are already implemented.\n\nI've finalized the mobile strategy, designing for a responsive layout where the bento grid stacks vertically on smaller screens, and sidebars collapse elegantly.\n\nI will focus on updating `app/portal/dashboard/page.tsx` entirely to introduce a premium client portal, and leave the landing page files untouched.\n\n\n**Refining Widget Integration**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on integrating the specific dashboard requirements. I'm focusing on incorporating the components as outlined. I will avoid any prohibited file modifications. I've re-reviewed the requirements, considering the requested data points, and considering that only pre-defined preview data should be utilized. I will ensure each widget is visually premium and clearly labeled as a preview. I am considering the mobile stacking strategy for the bento grid. I will stick to the allowed file modifications.\n\n\n**Leveraging Existing Components**\n\nI'm now cataloging pre-built components within `@/components/private-app` that are perfectly suited for dashboard integration, including `MetricTile`, `WorkspaceCard`, and others with premium styling. I plan to leverage these in the layout, adding additional visual elements, calls-to-action, and links. I will be looking closely at their import or export.\n\n\n\n**Importing Private App Components**\n\nI'm now confirming the seamless accessibility of pre-built components via `@/components/private-app` by reviewing `components/private-app/index.tsx`. I can directly import all of them, which will streamline the dashboard integration. This also simplifies the mapping of mock data to the data structures these components support.\n\n\n**Analyzing Component Props**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the imported component prop requirements to ensure a smooth data mapping process. Specifically, I'm examining `MetricTile`, `StatusBadge`, `PrivatePageHeader`, `AgentHealthCard`, and `ProjectCard`. I've outlined each component's required props, and I can start to match the `data-model.ts` data to them, or build customized versions directly on the dashboard to provide the exact links and layout required!\n\n\n**Mapping Data Structures**\n\nI'm now mapping the mock data to specific component props. I've reviewed `ProjectSpec` and have a clear understanding of its fields. Also, I've analyzed `DocumentCard`, `InvoiceCard`, and `SupportTicketCard` prop requirements. I confirmed that `AnalyticsPanel` and `GovernancePanel` are self-contained and don't need props, which streamlines integration. Finally, I'm noting the `ActivityFeed` uses `ActivityItem`, and I will map the required values.\n\n\n**Matching Data to Components**\n\nI'm now focusing on mapping the mock data to specific component props, specifically for the `ActivityFeed` and its underlying `ActivityItem`. I've analyzed available `previewProjects` from `lib/mock-data-model.ts` and can match properties like `id`, `name`, `status`, `desc`, `nodesCount`, and `lastUpdated` to the `ProjectCard`'s `ProjectSpec`. I have started constructing this map now.\n\n\n**Connecting Data Points**\n\nI'm now focusing on connecting `previewAgentOperations` to the `AgentSpec` for use in `AgentHealthCard`. I've confirmed the data model doesn't create type conflicts. I'm also considering adding links to all the key areas: Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, and Governance, both as quick links and within widget boxes. I am building a custom header block with a welcome message, account summary, and action CTAs. I'll add a visual warning.\n\n\n"}}
